com.gwtplatform.dispatch.annotation
Annotation Type GenProxy

@Target(value=TYPE)
@Retention(value=SOURCE)
@Inherited
public @interface GenProxy

Annotation to generate EntityProxy and ValueProxy classes.

Simply annotate your entity with GenProxy and gwt-platform will generate you a ProxyFor interface. The generated interface equals the given examples on DevGuideRequestFactory.


Generate


Fields as proxy:
You can declare fields as proxy using UseProxy or @UseProxyName.

If you type:

 
 @GenProxy
 public class Person {
   @UseProxyName("com.gwtplatform.dispatch.annotation.AddressProxy")
   Address address;
   @UseProxy(DetailProxy.class)
   Detail detail;
 }

gwt-platform will generate the following EntityProxy.

 
 @ProxyFor(com.gwtplatform.dispatch.annotation.Person.class)
 public interface PersonProxy extends EntityProxy {
   EntityProxyId<PersonProxy> stableId();

   com.gwtplatform.dispatch.annotation.AddressProxy getAddress();
   com.gwtplatform.dispatch.annotation.DetailProxy getDetail();

   void setAddress(com.gwtplatform.dispatch.annotation.AddressProxy address);
   void setDetail(com.gwtplatform.dispatch.annotation.DetailProxy detail);
 }

Using Value Proxies: Set isEmbeddedType() to true.


Note: If your package name contains ".server", the processor automatically replaces this with ".shared". To avoid this behaviour, set the target package manual using targetPackage().

Author:
Florian Sauter

targetPackage

public abstract String targetPackage
Defines the output package.

By default the output is generated to the same source folder.

If you are not using a custom target package, the processor will automatically replace ".server" in your package name with ".shared".

@GenProxy(targetPackage = "com.example.package.server")

Default:
""

filterGetter

public abstract String[] filterGetter
Add a property name to avoid the generation of a getter for this property.

@GenProxy(filterGetter = {"id", "customer"})

The properties "id" and "customer" will have no getters.

Default:
{}

filterSetter

public abstract String[] filterSetter
Add a property name to avoid the generation of a setter for this property.

@GenProxy(filterSetter = {"id", "customer"})

The properties "id" and "customer" will have no setters.

Default:
{}

isEmbeddedType

public abstract boolean isEmbeddedType
An embedded type results in a ValueProxy instead of an EntityProxy. By default, an EntityProxy is generated.

Default:
false

locator

public abstract Class<? extends Locator> locator
See Also:
ProxyFor#locator()
Default:
com.google.web.bindery.requestfactory.shared.Locator.class
